{
  "stem": "23626.4",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I met him when we were in the red house yet, in the red building downstairs, before the villa.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was working in a small building that had the incoming and outcoming water and the waste from the camps.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was in charge of the pipes that were controlling the water.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he worked at night.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he was very involved in the resistance group, because there was a room behind those pipes that they were hiding arms.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he was connected with one Ukrainian that he trusted.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he used to bring him arms, ammunition.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And Adam [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] actually asked me a couple of times, and I refused, to help out the resistance group by bringing out some documents that were in Goeth's drawers and passes for people to be able to get in and out from the camp.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I never spoke about it until a book came out, was written by Dr.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Alexander Bibovich who had a photographic mind and remembered everything that happened in the ghetto, in the camp.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he knew about our activity, about me, about Adam and others who were involved in that resistance group.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I didn't think I can speak about it, because it was so incredible for me to do what I did and taking such a big chances.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But after Adam asked me so many times, and I knew-- again, I was afraid that he will kill my sisters at the time, and other hundreds of hundreds of people-- that's what they used to do.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "When one did something wrong, against the law, they would take 50, 100 people and shoot them.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "That was his order.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
